  "root_text": {
    "an4.32:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4.32 ",
    "an4.32:0.2": "4. Cakkavagga ",
    "an4.32:0.3": "Saṅgahasutta ",
    "an4.32:1.1": "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, saṅgahavatthūni. ",
    "an4.32:1.2": "Katamāni cattāri? ",
    "an4.32:1.3": "Dānaṁ, peyyavajjaṁ, atthacariyā, samānattatā—",
    "an4.32:1.4": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri saṅgahavatthūnīti. ",
    "an4.32:2.1": "Dānañca peyyavajjañca, ",
    "an4.32:2.2": "atthacariyā ca yā idha; ",
    "an4.32:2.3": "Samānattatā ca dhammesu, ",
    "an4.32:2.4": "tattha tattha yathārahaṁ; ",
    "an4.32:2.5": "Ete kho saṅgahā loke, ",
    "an4.32:2.6": "rathassāṇīva yāyato. ",
    "an4.32:3.1": "Ete ca saṅgahā nāssu, ",
    "an4.32:3.2": "na mātā puttakāraṇā; ",
    "an4.32:3.3": "Labhetha mānaṁ pūjaṁ vā, ",
    "an4.32:3.4": "pitā vā puttakāraṇā. ",
    "an4.32:4.1": "Yasmā ca saṅgahā ete, ",
    "an4.32:4.2": "samavekkhanti paṇḍitā; ",
    "an4.32:4.3": "Tasmā mahattaṁ papponti, ",
    "an4.32:4.4": "pāsaṁsā ca bhavanti te”ti. ",
    "an4.32:4.5": "Dutiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an4.32:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 4.32 ",
    "an4.32:0.2": "4. Situations ",
    "an4.32:0.3": "Inclusion ",
    "an4.32:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these four ways of being inclusive. ",
    "an4.32:1.2": "What four? ",
    "an4.32:1.3": "Giving, kindly words, taking care, and equality. ",
    "an4.32:1.4": "These are the four ways of being inclusive. ",
    "an4.32:2.1": "Giving and kindly words, ",
    "an4.32:2.2": "taking care here, ",
    "an4.32:2.3": "and treating equally in worldly conditions, ",
    "an4.32:2.4": "as they deserve in each case. ",
    "an4.32:2.5": "These ways of being inclusive in the world ",
    "an4.32:2.6": "are like a moving chariot’s linchpin. ",
    "an4.32:3.1": "If there were no such ways of being inclusive, ",
    "an4.32:3.2": "neither mother nor father ",
    "an4.32:3.3": "would be respected and honored ",
    "an4.32:3.4": "for what they’ve done for their children. ",
    "an4.32:4.1": "But since these ways of being inclusive do exist, ",
    "an4.32:4.2": "the astute do regard them well, ",
    "an4.32:4.3": "so they achieve greatness ",
    "an4.32:4.4": "and are praised.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an4.32:0.3": "Saṅgahasutta → saṅgahavatthusuttaṁ (bj) ",
    "an4.32:4.1": "saṅgahā → saṅgahe (aṭṭhakathāyaṁ pāṭhantaraṁ) "
  },
